      • createLinkPoint

        ILinkPoint createLinkPoint(LinkPointKind kind,
                           Point location)
        Factory method to create an arbitrary ILinkPoint.

        The returned link point is not attached to the route. You may insert it into getAllPoints() or getBendPoints() .

        Parameters:
        kind - the link point kind
        location - the link point location. This location is copied.
        Returns:
        a new link point.

      • getAllPoints

        java.util.List<ILinkPoint> getAllPoints()
        Get a direct access to all points of the connection.

        The returned list is a direct reference, modifying it modifies the ILinkRoute. It does not modify the connection from which this path was built. The route must be applied to the IDiagramLink.setRoute(ILinkRoute).

        Returns:
        the points in coordinates relative to the diagram...

      • getBendPoints

        java.util.List<ILinkPoint> getBendPoints()
        Get a direct access to bend points of the connection.

        The returned list is a direct reference, modifying it modifies the ILinkRoute. It does not modify the connection from which this path was built. The route must be applied to the IDiagramLink.setRoute(ILinkRoute).

        Returns:
        the points in coordinates relative to the diagram...

      • removePoint

        void removePoint(int index)
        Removes the point at the specified position in this point list.

        Shifts any subsequent elements to the left (subtracts one from their indices).

        Parameters:
        index - the index of the element to be removed.

      • setSourceAnchor

        ILinkRoute setSourceAnchor(Point loc,
                           boolean sliding)
        Request to anchor the connection source point at a given location.

        The final anchor location may be different than the requested one. It may also depends on the adjacent bend point location.

        Call getSourceAnchor() to get the final location of the anchor.

        Parameters:
        loc - the point location
        sliding - true to request a sliding anchor, false for a fixed anchor
        Returns:
        this instance.

      • setTargetAnchor

        ILinkRoute setTargetAnchor(Point loc,
                           boolean sliding)
        Request to anchor the connection target point at a given location.

        The final anchor location may be different than the requested one. It may also depends on the adjacent bend point location.

        Call getTargetAnchor() to get the final location of the anchor.

        Parameters:
        loc - the point location
        sliding - true to request a sliding anchor, false for a fixed anchor
        Returns:
        this instance.
